│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue                                                             │
│                                                                                            │
│ The `slp-vectorizer` crashes with a segmentation fault when analyzing a function           │
│ containing an `insertvalue` instruction. The instruction operates on aggregate types       │
│ (structs) that are composed of other, empty, structs (`{}`). The crash occurs in the       │
│ `BoUpSLP::canMapToVector` function, a predicate used to determine if a given `Type` can be │
│ legally vectorized. The crash happens because the function makes an invalid assumption     │
│ when recursively analyzing nested struct types.                                            │
│                                                                                            │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log                                                               │
│                                                                                            │
│ The provided backtrace is the most critical piece of information:                          │
